##Chi Li, president of the Wuhan Federation of Literary and Art Circles: Hope to never repeat the mistakes made in the past

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Tang Qi, _ paper _ News, Wuhan

Chi Li

Chi Li, a famous writer and president of the Wuhan Literary Federation, was surprised to find so many readers for a novel she wrote more than 20 years ago in the winter and spring social season of 2020.

On Jan. 29, a netizen posted an excerpt of Chi Li's novel cholera, which he called a "divine prediction, " because it was a 1997 novella by Chi Li. In the memory of writing this novel, "It's a novel that comes from my own professional experience, " Chi Li wrote. "I was an epidemiologist for three years, and when I had to leave health and epidemic prevention, I thought I should write a novel about my concerns. "

Since December, a new outbreak of pneumonia has swept the country and the world, leaving no one behind. Chi Li in Wuhan, the epicenter of the outbreak, did her best to warn: "THE EPIDEMIC IS NO JOKE! It's not vegetarian! "

Chi Li wrote "six suggestions for properties and owners" on January 26, which was published in Chutian metropolis daily on February 1. These suggestions and appeals were later called "six tips for pools" by local media.

"I am one of the owners of this community. I have studied public health and participated in the containment and prevention of epidemics. In view of the fact that the epidemic is still growing in this city, but many owners have to go to the supermarket to buy vegetables because of food shortages. The supermarket is not only overcrowded, but even more frightening is human-to-human contact, which will cause further spread and spread, directly affecting the lives of you, your family and others, and leading to the abandonment of the Wuhan Quarantine,"Chi Li strongly recommended, wuhan's living quarters to take the "direct purchase of vegetable food package, the implementation of non-contact distribution. ".

In a recent interview with thepaper.cn, Chi Li said, "I started calling for quarantine from the very beginning of the Wuhan lockdown. The city is still full of cars and people, and supermarkets are rushing to buy them. Respiratory infections are quite severe, if you can not do crowd isolation, can not block transmission, "closed city" is meaningless. My call and my six tips on how to segregate at home are based on the most basic and fundamental principles of Infectious Disease Prevention."

"Man may ignore epidemics, but epidemics do not ignore man, and we have a price to pay for deceiving ourselves, " reads the title of cholera, which still has meaning for Chi Li. She believes that the most important issue in thinking about the prevention and control of the NCP epidemic is that we must abide by the Infectious Disease Prevention and treatment law, educate the public about this law and practice it.

"The same is true for the general public, as long as they know how to prevent and treat infectious diseases, they will not be so panic-stricken, " she said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Here's a conversation with Chi Li

"Our initial reaction was so slow. "

When did you first learn about the epidemic of NCP? When did the severity of the outbreak begin to be felt?

Chi Li: I've heard about this outbreak, about December of last year, from a friend. At that time my heart was a tick: is not there a certain respiratory infectious disease in the epidemic? When I was young, my first major was public health epidemiology, and I was very sensitive to infectious diseases. I was relieved when it became official that there was no proof of human-to-human transmission. But as the folklore grew more and more frightening, and the names were all true, my heart again said: The epidemic is no joke, it is not vegetarian, it is to eat people! At this point, I felt the severity of the outbreak. Sure enough, soon after, Wuhan suddenly announced "closed city. ".

What changes have taken place in your life and heart since the "city closure" of Wuhan on January 23? So far today, have you been out?

Chi Li: "closing the city" didn't come as a surprise to me. At the beginning of the mood more tightly, once "closed city" , my heart but down. My house was quarantined before the siege. In any case, infectious diseases, you'd rather believe in it, not the absence of it, early preparation, be prepared.

Originally, I was going out for the Spring Festival holiday. The high-speed train ticket had already been bought. We resolutely returned the ticket, immediately bought food and vegetables nearby, stuffed the refrigerator with them, and in general stored grain according to the normal 14-day quarantine period. I'm never going anywhere where there's a crowd. I also warned and warned my colleagues. So far, I've been pretty much isolated at home, so I don't leave the house for anything important, and if I have to leave the house, I do it first.

Thepaper.cn: What were the considerations that led you to call for days of effective quarantine and action in the community? What impresses you most about the measures taken so far, and why?

Chi Li: Wuhan "closed city" first, I began to call for quarantine. Because seeing the city sealed, sealed people, the city is still full of traffic and crowds, supermarkets rush to buy People Chung. Respiratory infections are quite severe, if you can not do crowd isolation, can not block transmission, "closed city" is meaningless. My appeal and my six tips on how to segregate at home are what my friends in the media jokingly call "six pools, " which are based on the most basic and fundamental principles of Infectious Disease Prevention and control.

If anything, it was a shock at how slow our initial response was. Pestilence is a flood monster, this understanding of ordinary people can not be, we professional public health system must not be without. For if it is slow, it is a great loss of life and property.

Has the spirit of the people of Wuhan changed in the face of the epidemic? Or, the people of Wuhan need to change something?

Chi Li: the epidemic swallowed up a specific life, I as a writer to shape the writing, but also a specific individual, in fact, there is no abstract "Wuhan people, " Therefore, it is impossible to say what the abstract Wuhan people need to change. And for each specific Wuhan people, I believe, after this plague, the state of mind must be changed. From the point of view of literary works, the works of the future will certainly be reflected. But literature is not so simple and straightforward, not like the kind of facebook users uploaded on the Internet.

"Man had better learn to live in harmony with everything. "

Thepaper.cn: You used to be an epidemiologist at the grassroots level. What impact has this experience of studying and working had on your response to the epidemic?

Chi Li: What you learn when you're young, often has a lifelong impact, in terms of the way you think and the way you live. In the face of this epidemic, I am a direct epidemic prevention and control of professional thinking.

The paper: Now that the seventh edition of the protocol has been released, do you think we have a complete understanding of the new coronavirus, what questions still need to be answered, and how should the public be informed?

Chi Li: Certainly not in its entirety. This is the diagnosis and treatment program, is clinical, is the treatment of this new disease stage of exploration. More importantly, the epidemiological tracking and blocking, should go hand in hand with the clinical and even more advanced, is the real prevention and control. For example, if enough clinical control data are available to show that the new coronavirus is likely to be passed through the faecal cavity as a result of oral transmission, it may be necessary to conduct a thorough examination of the faecal reservoir to open and seal it as soon as possible. Again, it's a big and difficult job, but it's also necessary to block transmission. As far as public awareness is concerned, the more transparent, the more extensive, and the more universal the knowledge, the better, so that everyone knows what they should do.

In the face of a new infectious disease, what kind of normal mechanism is needed to prevent the spread of the disease to the maximum extent?

Chi Li: there is a mechanism for normalisation, and there is one all over the world. Many countries have public health systems that invest more in research and equipment than in clinical medicine. CHINA HAS "Infectious Disease Prevention Law" , the law provides that infectious diseases are reported every day of the epidemic card. If you think about it, wouldn't it be normal to have a strict law on infectious diseases alone? If it is not ignored, if it is done in accordance with the law, the epidemic may be limited to solving the problem on a very small scale.

"human beings can ignore epidemics, but epidemics do not ignore human beings. We have to pay the price for deceiving ourselves, " the paper said. What new thinking and understanding do you have?

Chi Li: the New Thinking and recognition is that I suddenly found that this sentence of mine still continues to work.

The paper: How to understand the "eradication" OF INFECTIOUS DISEASES? When can not really "eliminate" , in the process of coexistence with nature, how human coexistence with potential crisis?

Chi Li: As I have written in the cholera, destruction is only a temporary interruption and termination. Humans don't own the earth, they live in harmony with everything. The food chain is a circular structure, where those who eat are not in order of size, but are prey to the weak, and viruses and bacteria are sometimes more powerful than humans. So it's best for humans to learn to live in harmony with everything, starting with respect.

What can be done about nature education and humanities education? How to strengthen the dissemination of common sense in public health in the future? How does a megacity like Wuhan deal with a public crisis like this?

Chi Li: There's a lot to think about this time. The most important thing is to abide by the law, popularize the law and practice the law, in accordance with the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases. For the general public, as well, as long as know the prevention and treatment of infectious diseases, it would not be so panic.

"I hope to rise from the ashes and never make the same mistakes. "

Will you write about the epidemic after it? What do you think is the greatest significance of disaster literature?

Chi Li: Literature is an aesthetic or ugly art, never a direct expression, direct expression is the function of the news. Of course, literary writing covers and cuts into social events. The significance of literature is that it is always Wu Wei, always in the eye of the beholder, always in the eye of the beholder, always in the eye of the beholder, always in the eye of the beholder. It means something to those who read, nothing to those who do not read; it means a great deal to those who empathize, and nothing more to those who do not.

What is the most important written record to be kept after a disaster? Post-disaster psychological reconstruction, how to use the power of words and other means to soothe the heart?

Chi Li: that's not what I think it is. Some literary works and words can stay, can placate people's hearts, is an objective occurrence, not the writer can predict. I had no idea, for example, that the cholera epidemic, which I wrote in 1997, would suddenly have so many readers today. All a writer has to do is work hard and write hard.

The paper: As we see the ups and downs of this epidemic, and the loss and rebirth of life, will the inherent features and emotions of the people of Wuhan Change after the epidemic? Will it affect your creation of Wuhan people? How should words or literary works record and write the value of life?

Chi Li: The epidemic is not over, and all judgments are premature. But here's the thing. It's not the first time mankind's suffered a disaster. Human beings have come a long way. Especially our Chinese nation, is a disaster-ridden, disaster-prone nation. This story, is an old and rewritten story, my writing, of course, will be affected and rewritten. The reason why I keep writing is that I hope that in the course of life, we can learn something, can be reborn after the fire, not to repeat the past.

An introduction to Chi Li

Chi Li, author, current chairman of the Wuhan Literary Federation, Member of the Presidium of the Chinese Writers Association. For the main novel, See Chi Li's classic collected works (9 volumes) . The main collections of essays are "boil to the drop of water into a bead" , "come to the children" , "Li" and "stone book" . There is Chi Li. 69. The latest novel, the Big Tree Bug. His work won the first Lu Xun Literary Prize and various awards. A film, a TV play, a play, an adaptation of several novels. There are foreign translations in various languages constantly published.

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
